    32вҶ’## Intro<a name="intro"></a>
    34вҶ’Tomli is a Python library for parsing [TOML](https://toml.io).
    35вҶ’Version 2.4.0 and later are compatible with [TOML v1.1.0](https://toml.io/en/v1.1.0).
    36вҶ’Older versions are [TOML v1.0.0](https://toml.io/en/v1.0.0) compatible.
    37вҶ’
    38вҶ’A version of Tomli, the `tomllib` module,
    39вҶ’was added to the standard library in Python 3.11
    40вҶ’via [PEP 680](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0680/).
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    50вҶ’## Installation<a name="installation"></a>
    52вҶ’```bash
    53вҶ’pip install tomli
    54вҶ’```
    55вҶ’
    56вҶ’## Usage<a name="usage"></a>
    58вҶ’### Parse a TOML string<a name="parse-a-toml-string"></a>
    60вҶ’```python
    61вҶ’import tomli
    62вҶ’
    63вҶ’toml_str = """
    64вҶ’[[players]]
    65вҶ’name = "Lehtinen"
    66вҶ’number = 26
    67вҶ’
    68вҶ’[[players]]
    69вҶ’name = "Numminen"
    70вҶ’number = 27
    71вҶ’"""
    72вҶ’
    73вҶ’toml_dict = tomli.loads(toml_str)
    74вҶ’assert toml_dict == {
    75вҶ’    "players": [{"name": "Lehtinen", "number": 26}, {"name": "Numminen", "number": 27}]
    76вҶ’}
    77вҶ’```
    78вҶ’
   152вҶ’## FAQ<a name="faq"></a>
   154вҶ’### Why this parser?<a name="why-this-parser"></a>
   156вҶ’- it's lil'
   157вҶ’- pure Python with zero dependencies
   158вҶ’- the fastest pure Python parser [\*](#pure-python):
   159вҶ’  14x as fast as [tomlkit](https://pypi.org/project/tomlkit/),
   160вҶ’  2.1x as fast as [toml](https://pypi.org/project/toml/)
   161вҶ’- outputs [basic data types](#how-do-toml-types-map-into-python-types) only
   162вҶ’- 100% spec compliant: passes all tests in
   163вҶ’  [toml-lang/toml-test](https://github.com/toml-lang/toml-test)
   164вҶ’  test suite
   165вҶ’- thoroughly tested: 100% branch coverage
   166вҶ’
   201вҶ’## Performance<a name="performance"></a>
   203вҶ’The `benchmark/` folder in this repository contains a performance benchmark for comparing the various Python TOML parsers.
   204вҶ’
   205вҶ’Below are the results for commit [064e492](https://github.com/hukkin/tomli/tree/064e492919b2338def788753b8c981c9131334c0).
